# TypeScript & React

## Components

```tsx
export function AboutMe(): React.ReactElement {
  return <section id="about-me-container" className="page-container">...</section>
}
```

- Named exports, functional components with hooks
- `React.ReactElement` return type (not `JSX.Element`)
- Interfaces for props (prefer over type aliases)
- Strict null checks; avoid `any`

## Imports (Prettier-enforced order)

1. External packages
2. `components/...`
3. `assets/...`
4. `data/...`
5. `types/...`
6. `styles/...css`

Use absolute imports from `src` — configured in `tsconfig.json` and `vite.config.ts`.

## Formatting

Single quotes, no semicolons, 140 char lines, 2-space indent, LF endings.

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<button>`, etc.)
- ARIA labels on custom interactive elements
- `onKeyDown` handlers when using non-button click targets
- Keyboard focus management for modals/menus

## File naming

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `AboutMe.tsx` |
| Data | camelCase | `experiences.ts` |
| Types | `*.types.ts` | `project.types.ts` |
| Hooks | `use*.ts` | `useTheme.ts` |
